title: Abdul Qadir Patel wins NA-243 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians candidate Abdul Qadir Patel has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-243 Kimari-II by securing 60,266 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Shujat Ali an independent candidate who bagged 48,690 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 37.49 percent.
